HEADWORD: Melassic
<hw>Me*las"sic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Molasses</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, an acid obtained from molasses or glucose, and probably
identical with <altname>saccharic</altname> acid (also called
<altname>D-glucaric</altname> acid or
<altname>tetrahydroxyadipic</altname> acid). See
<er>Saccharic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

